{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-06-07T21:08:25.965Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file__write_file_1780866505964_0","parameters":{"content":"# Downloaded Papers\n\n1. **[From Text to Space: Mapping Abstract Spatial Models in LLMs during a Grid-World Navigation Task](2502.16690_From_Text_to_Space.pdf)**\n   - Authors: Martorell et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - arXiv: 2502.16690\n   - Why relevant: Investigates how LLMs represent spatial info (Cartesian representations) and tracks agent position.\n\n2. **[11PLUS-Bench: Demystifying Multimodal LLM Spatial Reasoning](2410.06468_11PLUS-Bench.pdf)**\n   - Authors: Li et al.\n   - Year: 2024/2025\n   - arXiv: 2410.06468\n   - Why relevant: Standardized spatial aptitude tests for MLLMs.\n\n3. **[Narrative-to-Scene Generation: Connecting Story Text to Playable Visual Environments](2403.15698_Narrative_to_Scene.pdf)**\n   - Authors: arXiv:2403.15698\n   - Year: 2024\n   - arXiv: 2403.15698\n   - Why relevant: Connects narrative text to spatial consistency and visual scenes.\n\n4. **[Socioverse: A World Model for Social Simulation](2504.10157_Socioverse.pdf)**\n   - Authors: Zhang et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - arXiv: 2504.10157\n   - Why relevant: Explores agent navigation in a world model.\n\n5. **[A Survey of Spatial Reasoning in LLM](2504.05786_Survey_Spatial_Reasoning.pdf)**\n   - Authors: Zha et al.\n   - Year: 2025\n   - arXiv: 2504.05786\n   - Why relevant: Comprehensive survey of the field.\n\n6. **[When LLMs Step into the 3D World: A Survey and Meta-Analysis](2405.10255_When_LLMs_Step_into_3D.pdf)**\n   - Authors: Ma et al.\n   - Year: 2024\n   - arXiv: 2405.10255\n   - Why relevant: Meta-analysis of LLMs in 3D environments.\n","file_path":"papers/README.md"}}
